</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33874AA69272A79B1BCFD15152EFE1B" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9D272169272A79B1BCFD15152EFE1B" blockId="8.[189,1399,721,959]" lastBlockId="9.[189,1399,267,505]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
This pantropical genus comprises almost 25 species which are mostly terrestrial (and a few epiphytic) ferns displaying erect, large, highly-divided fronds on a short-creeping (or long-creeping in some Asiatic species) to erect stout rhizomes bearing numerous robust roots (
<figureCitation id="13193BA469272A78B2FBFCD3154BFCD2" box="[1018,1090,791,817]" captionStart="Fig. 4" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1887,1913]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,1000,1847]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[189,1399,1000,1847]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 4. Terrestrial Comorian Hymenophyllaceae. A. Abrodictyum pseudorigidum Bauret &amp; Dubuisson, first identified as A. rigidum (Sw.) Ebihara &amp; Dubuisson, (F. Rakotondrainibe et al. 6771, P 00312031). B. Trichomanes boivinii Bosch, new for the archipelago according to the last inventories (as discussed in text) (F. Rakotondrainibe et al. 6675, P 00311390). Scale bar for both species = 3 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/896411/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). All Comorian specimens represent only one species although they are identified as either 
<taxonomicName id="4C225CA269272A78B2ACFCFF147FFCB7" authority="(Sw.) Ebihara &amp; Dubuisson" authorityName="(Sw.) Ebihara &amp; Dubuisson" box="[941,1398,826,853]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Abrodictyum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rigidum">
<emphasis id="B956FB3369272A78B2ACFCFF1522FCB7" box="[941,1067,826,853]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">A. rigidum</emphasis>
(Sw.) Ebihara &amp; Dubuisson
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="4C225CA269272A78B1E1FC9A1256FC9B" authority="(Desv.) Ebihara &amp; Dubuisson. These" authorityName="(Desv.) Ebihara &amp; Dubuisson. These" box="[224,863,862,888]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Trichomanes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cupressoides">
<emphasis id="B956FB3369272A78B1E1FC9A1090FC9B" box="[224,409,862,888]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">A. cupressoides</emphasis>
(Desv.) Ebihara &amp; Dubuisson. These
</taxonomicName>
two species are indeed commonly confused in collections. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB35AD069272A78B078FC451311FC7F" author="Kuhn F. A. M." box="[377,536,897,924]" journalOrPublisher="Engelman, Leipzig" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refString="Kuhn F. A. M. 1868. Filices Africanae. Engelman, Leipzig." title="Filices Africanae" type="book" year="1868">Kuhn (1868)</bibRefCitation>
also cited 
<taxonomicName id="4C225CA269272A78B3ACFC45152DFC78" authority="Blume" authorityName="Blume" authorityYear="1828" box="[685,1060,897,923]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Trichomanes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="obscurum">
<emphasis id="B956FB3369272A78B3ACFC4512CEFC78" box="[685,967,897,923]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Trichomanes obscurum</emphasis>
Blume
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName id="4C225CA269272A78B55CFC45131DFC5C" authority="(Blume) Ebihara &amp; K. Iwats." authorityName="(Blume) Ebihara &amp; K.Iwats." class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Abrodictyum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="obscurum">
<emphasis id="B956FB3369272A78B55CFC45147EFC78" box="[1117,1399,897,923]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Abrodictyum obscurum</emphasis>
(Blume) Ebihara &amp; K.Iwats.
</taxonomicName>
) for Mayotte, but this species is in fact restricted to Asia and is clearly distinct even if also often confused with 
<taxonomicName id="4C225CA269262A79B3BEFEC8124BFEC6" box="[703,834,267,294]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Abrodictyum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rigidum">
<emphasis id="B956FB3369262A79B3BEFEC8124BFEC6" box="[703,834,267,294]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">A. rigidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Recent morphological and molecular studies focused on 
<taxonomicName id="4C225CA269262A79B046FEEB10F7FEAA" box="[327,510,303,329]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Trichomanes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cupressoides">
<emphasis id="B956FB3369262A79B046FEEB10F7FEAA" box="[327,510,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">A. cupressoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and paleotropical 
<taxonomicName id="4C225CA269262A79B3DDFEEB1252FEAA" box="[732,859,303,329]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Abrodictyum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rigidum">
<emphasis id="B956FB3369262A79B3DDFEEB1252FEAA" box="[732,859,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">A. rigidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
evidenced that 
<taxonomicName id="4C225CA269262A79B516FEEB15C6FEAA" box="[1047,1231,303,329]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Trichomanes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cupressoides">
<emphasis id="B956FB3369262A79B516FEEB15C6FEAA" box="[1047,1231,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">A. cupressoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to Seychelles and is in fact nested within the distinct genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C225CA269262A79B251FE9615DCFE8E" authority="(Bauret et al. 2015)" authorityName="Bauret et al." authorityYear="2015" box="[848,1237,338,365]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Trichomanes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B956FB3369262A79B251FE9612E1FE8F" box="[848,1000,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Trichomanes</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB35AD069262A79B2F7FE9615C4FE8E" author="Bauret L. &amp; Grall A. &amp; Senterre B. &amp; Rouhan G. &amp; Hennequin S. &amp; Ebihara A. &amp; Dubuisson J. - Y." box="[1014,1229,338,365]" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="1 - 14" part="202" publicationUrl="http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.202.1.1" refString="Bauret L., Grall A., Senterre B., Rouhan G., Hennequin S., Ebihara A. &amp; Dubuisson J. - Y. 2015. New circumscription of Trichomanes cupressoides Desvaux (Hymenophyllaceae), an endemic filmy fern from Seychelles (Indian Ocean), and new insights into the genus Abrodictyum C. Presl in the western Indian Ocean. Phytotaxa 202: 1 - 14. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 202.1.1" title="New circumscription of Trichomanes cupressoides Desvaux (Hymenophyllaceae), an endemic filmy fern from Seychelles (Indian Ocean), and new insights into the genus Abrodictyum C. Presl in the western Indian Ocean" type="journal article" year="2015">
Bauret 
<emphasis id="B956FB3369262A79B54DFE97158FFE8F" box="[1100,1158,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">et al.</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C225CA269262A79B5DEFE9610ABFE6C" authority="Desv." authorityName="Desv." class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Trichomanes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cupressoides">
<emphasis id="B956FB3369262A79B5DEFE96105AFE6C" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Trichomanes cupressoides</emphasis>
Desv.
</taxonomicName>
is thus absent from Comoros. Furthermore, specimens of the Malagasy region (including Comoros) formerly identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C225CA269262A79B3BBFE5D123EFE51" box="[698,823,408,435]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Abrodictyum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rigidum">
<emphasis id="B956FB3369262A79B3BBFE5D123EFE51" box="[698,823,408,435]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">A. rigidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
actually represent a distinct species from the true neotropical 
<taxonomicName id="4C225CA269262A79B046FE7813B9FE35" authority="(Bauret et al. 2015)" authorityName="Bauret et al." authorityYear="2015" box="[327,688,443,470]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Abrodictyum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rigidum">
<emphasis id="B956FB3369262A79B046FE7810CDFE36" box="[327,452,443,470]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">A. rigidum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB35AD069262A79B0D3FE7F13A1FE35" author="Bauret L. &amp; Grall A. &amp; Senterre B. &amp; Rouhan G. &amp; Hennequin S. &amp; Ebihara A. &amp; Dubuisson J. - Y." box="[466,680,443,470]" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="1 - 14" part="202" publicationUrl="http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.202.1.1" refString="Bauret L., Grall A., Senterre B., Rouhan G., Hennequin S., Ebihara A. &amp; Dubuisson J. - Y. 2015. New circumscription of Trichomanes cupressoides Desvaux (Hymenophyllaceae), an endemic filmy fern from Seychelles (Indian Ocean), and new insights into the genus Abrodictyum C. Presl in the western Indian Ocean. Phytotaxa 202: 1 - 14. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 202.1.1" title="New circumscription of Trichomanes cupressoides Desvaux (Hymenophyllaceae), an endemic filmy fern from Seychelles (Indian Ocean), and new insights into the genus Abrodictyum C. Presl in the western Indian Ocean" type="journal article" year="2015">
Bauret 
<emphasis id="B956FB3369262A79B328FE78136AFE36" box="[553,611,443,469]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">et al.</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, and this new species has recently been described and named 
<taxonomicName id="4C225CA269262A79B1BCFE1B1529FE1A" authority="Bauret &amp; Dubuisson (Dubuisson et al. 2016)" authorityName="Bauret &amp; Dubuisson (Dubuisson et al." authorityYear="2016" box="[189,1056,478,505]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Abrodictyum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pseudorigidum">
<emphasis id="B956FB3369262A79B1BCFE1B1302FE1A" box="[189,523,479,505]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Abrodictyum pseudorigidum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB35AD069262A79B313FE1B1529FE1A" author="Dubuisson J. - Y. &amp; Bauret L. &amp; Grall A. &amp; Li T. &amp; Ebihara A. &amp; Hennequin S." box="[530,1056,478,505]" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="151 - 168" part="284" publicationUrl="http://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.284.3.1" refString="Dubuisson J. - Y., Bauret L., Grall A., Li T., Ebihara A. &amp; Hennequin S. 2016. Discussion on the taxonomy of African fern Abrodictyum rigidum (Sw.) Ebihara &amp; Dubuisson and description of two new Abrodictyum C. Presl species (Hymenophyllaceae, Polypodiidae) for the Afro-Malagasy region. Phytotaxa 284: 151 - 168. http: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 284.3.1" title="Discussion on the taxonomy of African fern Abrodictyum rigidum (Sw.) Ebihara &amp; Dubuisson and description of two new Abrodictyum C. Presl species (Hymenophyllaceae, Polypodiidae) for the Afro-Malagasy region" type="journal article" year="2016">
Bauret &amp; Dubuisson (Dubuisson 
<emphasis id="B956FB3369262A79B298FE1B12DDFE1A" box="[921,980,479,505]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">et al.</emphasis>
2016)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
